: classify dup 0 > if "+" . else dup 0 < if "-" . else "z" . then then drop ;
5 classify cr
-5 classify cr
0 classify cr
: countdown 0 begin 1 + dup . dup 3 = until drop cr ;
countdown
: tagged 0 begin 1 + dup . dup 4 = if drop exit then again ;
tagged cr

\ a closer with no matching opener errors instead of patching an arbitrary
\ dictionary cell (a bare `200 then` once silently wrote dict[200]); each line
\ is its own REPL entry, and the dictionary stays intact afterward
200 then
200 else
200 until
200 200 repeat
3 4 + . cr
